# Pinned commit of github.com/mstan/snesrecomp used to build this repo.
# Bumping this is a deliberate, reviewable change (snesrecomp is a separate
# repo evolving on its own cadence). Update via:
#   git -C ../snesrecomp rev-parse main > /tmp/sha && \
#     sed -i "s|^sha = .*|sha = $(cat /tmp/sha)|" snesrecomp.pin
sha = ccd78f976efe19e073ea4736c3107894d700dc7b
# 2026-07-14 DerrickGold candidate integration: SimpleHDMA bounds, generated
# bank sharding, opt-in widescreen policies, no-sprite-limits support, and the
# filtered interpreter hook used by SMW's user-validated 16:9 spawn window.
# 2026-07-14 bump (88c41ad -> f6e3001): preserve guest non-local returns
# across direct AOT/interpreter bounces. Fresh atomic regen and a 35k-frame
# LLE title-attract soak completed with Mario alive, normal visuals, advancing
# heartbeats, and no bail/trap/watchdog diagnostics.
# 2026-07-13 LLE-first redesign checkpoint (8c14fc1 -> 88c41ad):
# deterministic atomic manifest emission, exact architectural AOT/LLE
# boundaries, RTI-aware mixed-tier interrupts, safe profile roots, and HLE
# overlays that cover every runtime M/X mode without leaking tail metadata.
# 2026-07-13 bump (11e11fe -> 8c14fc1): CPU-to-SPC port writes now use
# hardware-immediate visibility by default. The host wall-time deferred path
# remains only as an explicit diagnostic override, keeping APU semantics
# independent of the LLE/HLE scheduler tier. Runner-only; no bank regen.
# 2026-07-13 bump (2ae1488 -> 11e11fe): shared first-class LLE execution-mode
# policy plus mixed interpreted/compiled stack continuations, interrupt-owned
# memory/input poll yields, and return-PC guards validated by Super Metroid.
# Runner/compiler only; SMW generated banks remain unchanged.
# 2026-06-13 bump (26063a0 -> 2ae1488): add the shared RmlUi pre-boot
# launcher module (runner/src/launcher/) + RmlUi/FreeType submodules.
# Companion SMW side wires the launcher (smw.vcxproj, main.c GameInfo,
# config WriteConfigFile) and bundles the SMW MSU-1 driver. Runner-only
# for the engine; src/gen untouched (the launcher needs no regen).
# 2026-06-13 bump (3369264 -> 26063a0): pick up MSU-1 coprocessor support
# (843f7d3, default-OFF/byte-identical unless SNESRECOMP_MSU1 is set), the
# permissive multi-hash ROM resolver (f716b4a) and ASCII-only launcher
# warnings (a887514), plus the MSVC build fix for msu1.c's dir-scan (26063a0,
# FindFirstFile branch — a887514's <dirent.h> use did not compile on MSVC).
# smw.vcxproj gains msu1.c. Runner-only, src/gen untouched (no regen).
# 2026-06-12 bump (f63de71 -> 3369264): ppu widescreen BG3 widen. New opt-in
# PpuSetWidescreenBg3Widen(ppu, from_y): on scanlines >= from_y, BG3 (layer 2)
# gets the same side-margin extension as BG1/BG2 instead of staying clamped to
# 256. SMW draws in-level water on BG3, so the old clamp (kept for the BG3
# status bar) clipped the water to 4:3 — it stopped at the authentic edge while
# the rest of the scene filled 16:9. Runner-only, src/gen untouched (no regen).
# Default 0 = off, so Zelda/MMX rendering is byte-unchanged; SMW opts in with
# its 40px HUD band height. Companion SMW main.c calls the setter in-level.
# User-verified live: water now fills the full widescreen view.
# 2026-06-12 bump (c17bef7 -> f63de71): merge feat/shadow-enhancements —
# opt-in S-DSP cubic audio + CRT color LUT, all default OFF. Adds three
# framework sources (snes/dsp_shadow.c, snes/audio_shadow.c,
# snes/color_lut.c) that the runner build must now compile/link; SMW's
# src/smw.vcxproj is updated in the same commit to include them (the
# tip was unbuildable against SMW until then). No regen needed — gen
# output is unchanged; shadow/LUT paths are runtime-gated and off.
# 2026-06-11 bump (bf64f0d -> c17bef7): docs-only delta
# (ISSUES.md turbo music-drop note). No code, no regen, no rebuild.
# Unifies SMW/MMX/ALttP on the runner main tip ahead of the Zelda
# widescreen work (all forks descend from this single tip).
# 2026-06-11 bump (8ffc797 -> bf64f0d): follow-up — port-clock caps now
# scale with the observed audio-burst quantum (audio_samples is
# user-tunable; a burst larger than the latency ceiling would have
# re-collapsed command spacing). No behavior change at the default.
# 2026-06-11 bump (cbf7fa7 -> 8ffc797): pulls the APU port-write
# scheduler — the missed-SFX root-cause fix. Runner-only for CODE, but
# NOTE TWO COMPANION FACTS for anyone rebuilding:
#  - The v2 emitter now names its outputs src/gen/bank*_v2.c +
#    dispatch_v2.c (was smw_*_v2.c). This SMW commit renames the
#    vcxproj references and regen.sh accordingly; regenerate (or rename
#    your local gitignored src/gen files) before building. Gen CONTENT
#    at this pin is byte-identical to the previous build — verified by
#    full regen + cmp during the SFX investigation.
#  - tools/regen.sh now exits non-zero at the framework's stub lint:
#    SMW's 41 long-standing loud-trapped debt markers (8 unresolved
#    indirect-dispatch sites and friends, all verified 0-fire) now
#    hard-fail the gate. The banks ARE fully emitted before the gate
#    fires. Closing those sites is a separate recompiler campaign.
# The fix itself: CPU APU-port writes are scheduled in APU-sample time
# (write-clock targets, queue drained in apu_cycle) instead of mutating
# inPorts at wall time. Root cause was the 60.0988 Hz NMI beating
# against the 60.00 Hz audio-callback SPC bursts: when phases crossed,
# a sound command lived ~9 samples of APU time (engine polls every 64)
# and was silently dropped — seconds-long alternating runs of missed
# SFX. Always-on port-traffic rings (audio_events filter=2) + per-port
# cpu_port_overwrites counters land with it; tools/sfx_probe.py
# classifies every command SEEN/SEEN-NOKON/LOST. User-verified: 100%
# audio success across two full runs post-fix.
# 2026-06-11 bump (2b135e8 -> cbf7fa7): pulls the widescreen runner
# support, runner-only (src/gen untouched, no regen required). All
# changes are runtime-gated and inert unless the game opts in:
#  - debug server: always-on OAM write + render-read ring buffers
#    (2b6b5fc): oam_state / oam_write_get / oam_render_get commands.
#  - ppu: sprite-level x gate widened to the left widescreen margin
#    (239e2cb): x + spriteSize > -ppu->extraLeftCur (authentic
#    behavior unchanged when extraLeftCur == 0).
#  - ppu: opt-in widescreen HUD split for BG3 (4a3e1a4 + cbf7fa7):
#    PpuSetWidescreenHudSplit(); keys off the computed window set
#    (win.nr==1 && win.bits==0), not TMW bits. Fields zero on reset;
#    caller re-applies per frame. Ppu struct fields added BEFORE the
#    snapshot region — savestate layout unchanged.
# Companion SMW-side widescreen feature (Widescreen/WidescreenHud
# config, apply_overrides.py game-logic patches) landed on SMW main
# at the same time (3c0b794 -> ddac4fa).
